  "local_port": 55730,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the Staff Selection Commission (SSC) conducts various examinations to recruit staff for different posts in various ministries, departments, and organizations of the Government of India. Some of the prominent postings under SSC include:\n\n1. **SSC Combined Graduate Level Examination (CGL):**\n   - Assistant in Ministries/Departments\n   - Inspector (Central Excise, Preventive Officer, Examiner)\n   - Assistant Enforcement Officer in Directorate of Enforcement\n   - Income Tax Inspector\n   - Sub-Inspector in Central Bureau of Narcotics\n   - Divisional Accountant in various offices\n   - Auditor in offices under C&AG, CGDA, etc.\n\n2. **SSC Combined Higher Secondary Level Examination (CHSL):**\n   - Lower Division Clerk (LDC)\n   - Junior Secretariat Assistant (JSA)\n   - Postal Assistant (PA) / Sorting Assistant (SA)\n   - Data Entry Operator (DEO)\n\n3. **SSC Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS):**\n   - General Central Service Group 'C' Non-Gazetted, Non-Ministerial post such as Peon, Daftary, Jamadar, Junior Gestetner Operator, Farash, Chowkidar, Safaiwala, Mali, etc.\n\n4. **SSC Junior Engineer (JE) Examination:**\n   - Junior Engineer (Civil, Electrical, Mechanical) in Central Water Commission, CPWD, MES, etc.\n\n5. **SSC Stenographer Grade C and D Examination:**\n   - Stenographer in various Ministries/Departments of the Government of India, including in the offices of Indian Parliament.\n\n6. **SSC Constable (GD) Examination:**\n   - Constable General Duty (GD) in BSF, CISF, CRPF, SSB, NIA, SSF, and Rifleman in Assam Rifles.\n\n7. **SSC Junior Hindi Translator (JHT):**\n   - Junior Hindi Translator/Senior Hindi Translator in various Offices/Departments.\n\n8. **SSC Selection Posts:**\n   - Various Group B and Group C posts in different Ministries, Departments, and Organizations, based on regional requirements.\n\nThese are some of the major examinations conducted by SSC for various postings. Detailed and specific updates might vary year by year, so it is advisable to check the official SSC website or relevant notifications for the most current and specific information.",
